# Project stack — this repository

This repo is **Copilot Collections** (upstream `tsh-*` prompts, agents, skills) with an **Eversis Cursor port** under `prompts/`, `.cursor/rules/`, and `documentation/cursor-collection.md`.

| Area | This repository |
| ---- | --------------- |
| **Product** | Opinionated GitHub Copilot setup + published workflow docs |
| **Docs site** | Docusaurus 3 under **`website/`** (`copilot-collections-docs`) |
| **Cursor port** | Root **`prompts/public/`** and **`prompts/internal/`** (`eversis-*.md`) |
| **Upstream prompts** | **`.github/prompts/`** and **`.github/internal-prompts/`** (source for ports) |

## Quality commands (this repo)

Run from **`website/`** (see [website/package.json](website/package.json)):

- **Dev server:** `npm start` (Docusaurus)
- **Production build:** `npm run build` — use this as the primary quality gate for doc changes
- **Serve build locally:** `npm run serve`

There is no root `lint` / `test` script; the site is mostly Markdown and React theme.

## Conventions

- Feature specs for *downstream* or experimental work: **`docs/specs/*.spec.md`**
- Internal notes: **`docs/context/*.md`**
- **Template** for other projects: see **“Reference: Eversis stack example”** in [documentation/cursor-collection.md](../../documentation/cursor-collection.md)
